Day 3 of my 120datadayswithTina
The project I reviewed was the HR dashboard that I built a month ago. And seeing that dashboard, I asked myself, what was the first thing I did? Did I even pass through the data analysis stages of asking questions and defining my objectives? Or did I just build a dashboard for building sake?

But right now, I can say there is growth. Because if I want to build a dashboard now, I try to find the objective first. I look at how useful the dashboard will be. I go for clarity now. And that is growth, which Iâ€™m grateful for.

So cheers to building dashboards that are useful. Cheers to building dashboards that have clarity. Cheers to building dashboards that solve business problems.

